c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe open world role-playing Assassin’s Creed video game series is one of the most successful series of all time, praised for its in-depth use of historical characters and events, compelling graphics, and addictive gameplay. Assassin’s Creed games offer up the possibility of exploring history, mythology, and heritage immersively, graphically, and imaginatively. This collection of essays by architects archaeologists and historiansexplores the learning opportunities of playing, modifying, and extending the games in the classroom, on location, in the architectural studio, and in a museum.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAssassin’s Creed. 4aGeschichtsvermittlung. 4aKulturelles Erbe. 4aVideo Spiele.  aauthenticity.  acultural heritage.  ateaching.  avideo games.  aviolence.1 aBazile, Julien A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCameron, Hamish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChampion, Erik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChampion, Erik, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDubé, Adam K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrufstedt, Ylva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiriart Vera, Juan Francisco, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHiriart, Juan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoughton, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Kira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLacour, Rafael de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLefrançois, David, econtributor.4ctb4http